{
    "name": "Bee-Man of Bellis",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Vernon Vestha was a forest oracle obsessed with bees, reading the future in the patterns of their flight. Driven mad by a desire to internalize the bees\u2019 powers of divination, he became one with his beloved bees in some honeyed rite. Now a living swarm in the rough semblance of a man, Vernon still roams the forests near Bellis, and some still seek out the ex-druid\u2019s wisdom by calling his name (Knowledge [local] DC 20 to know). He often appears when he is called, though he seldom grants favors without exacting a terrible price."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This shabby-cloaked figure is surrounded by hundreds of bees.</i>",
